    <string
        name="setting_description_weather_api_keys">The application uses the accuweather server to display the weather. To have access to the API, you need to obtain a key for the application on the website https://developer.accuweather.com/user/me/apps \n\nYou can enter several API Keys to avoid blocking from the API, because the maximum number of requests per day is 50.
    </string>
    <string name="setting_description_weather_city_key_1">Click to select a location</string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_weather_city_key_2">A locality can only be selected if there is at least one API key
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_weather_language">The default is the system locale. Also affects the search string of the locality
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_text_calendar_enabled">From top to bottom, the day will be displayed first in large numbers, then the month, then the year
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_grid_calendar_enabled">If enabled, a calendar in tabular form will be displayed below the text calendar, with holidays from the production calendar, if enabled, plotted on it.
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_prod_calendar_is_russia">Unfortunately, at the moment, it is possible to show the production calendar only for Russia
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_prod_calendar_russia_region">Click to select a region of the Russian Federation to display regional holidays in the production calendar
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_prod_calendar_day_description_enabled">If enabled, the name of the holiday on the current day will be displayed between the text and table calendars, if there is one in the production calendar
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_dots_flash_animated">If enabled, the seconds dots will fade in and out every second. Not recommended for old devices!
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_hourly_beep_enabled">If enabled, every hour during the selected period a peak will sound like in a Casio watch
    </string>
    <string
        name="setting_description_hourly_beep_hours_range">The start hour must start from zero and not be greater than 22, the end hour must be greater than the start hour and less than, or equal to 23
    </string>
